the code using a computer.

00:00:55.350 --> 00:00:57.800
They didn't get very
far either.

00:00:57.800 --> 00:01:01.230
This is an interesting sort of
problem because it requires

00:01:01.230 --> 00:01:04.269
you to think in a slightly
different direction than

00:01:04.269 --> 00:01:07.190
you're accustomed to thinking,
and therefore it's a little

00:01:07.190 --> 00:01:08.700
bit amusing.

00:01:08.700 --> 00:01:13.020
This is not my creation, it
came from a book by a man

00:01:13.020 --> 00:01:15.730
named Polya, the title of the
book is Mathematics and

00:01:15.730 --> 00:01:17.640
Plausible Reasoning.

00:01:17.640 --> 00:01:21.360
And he gives this as an example
of a problem that can

00:01:21.360 --> 00:01:22.780
be solved only if
you think in a

00:01:22.780 --> 00:01:25.100
slightly different direction.

00:01:25.100 --> 00:01:28.450
I'll give you another example
of a problem from his book.

00:01:28.450 --> 00:01:33.520
Suppose, not that the problem
arises in this era when you do

00:01:33.520 --> 00:01:37.550
all of your graphics on a
computer console, but suppose

00:01:37.550 --> 00:01:41.160
you had to, in solving a problem
in short notice, draw

00:01:41.160 --> 00:01:47.800
a circle that had a diameter
of 4 inches.

00:01:47.800 --> 00:01:51.300
And you went looking for your
pair of compasses which you

00:01:51.300 --> 00:01:54.820
never use very often, and when
you found them, they were

00:01:54.820 --> 00:01:58.380
rusted solid, and they
were open to a

00:01:58.380 --> 00:02:01.300
distance of 5 inches.

00:02:01.300 --> 00:02:02.370
OK, so there's the problem.

00:02:02.370 --> 00:02:04.840
You have a pair of compasses
that can only draw a circle

00:02:04.840 --> 00:02:09.180
that's 5 inches in diameter, you
must draw a circle that's

00:02:09.180 --> 00:02:11.130
4 inches in diameter.

00:02:11.130 --> 00:02:13.890
What sort of construction, what
sort of mapping out of

00:02:13.890 --> 00:02:17.650
arcs that you connected together
could you do to

00:02:17.650 --> 00:02:21.910
create the circle of
smaller diameter?

00:02:21.910 --> 00:02:23.160
Anybody have an idea?

00:02:25.850 --> 00:02:28.960
It seems impossible
doesn't it?

00:02:28.960 --> 00:02:33.600
Well suppose you got yourself
a little block of wood that

00:02:33.600 --> 00:02:39.480
had a height that was equal to
the square root of 5 squared

00:02:39.480 --> 00:02:42.460
minus 4 squared.

00:02:42.460 --> 00:02:45.170
And so you have one end of the
compass is up on top of the

00:02:45.170 --> 00:02:49.580
block of wood the other end of
the compass traces out a

00:02:49.580 --> 00:02:52.450
circle that has a smaller
diameter.

00:02:52.450 --> 00:02:53.960
It's fairly obvious.

00:02:53.960 --> 00:02:57.530
But what you have to do is to
think of a problem that has

00:02:57.530 --> 00:03:00.630
poked your nose into
two-dimensions and think of it

00:03:00.630 --> 00:03:02.380
in terms of a three-dimensional
problem, and

00:03:02.380 --> 00:03:03.830
then the answer is easy.

00:03:03.830 --> 00:03:06.140
So that was the sort of thought
provoking thing that

00:03:06.140 --> 00:03:10.870
Polya presented in one
portion of this book.

00:03:10.870 --> 00:03:15.200
OK, if you enjoyed that problem,
